#1MillionLights means One million stories. Did you know that over 1 billion people live without access to energy? Little Sun is a small portable solar lamp designed to bring light to school children and their families living in areas of the world where electricity is not a given. The project was launched by artist Olafur Eliasson and they have now sold One Million lamps! For every lamp sold, another one is delivered to someone in urgent need of light! Follow @littlesunenergy, buy yourself a lamp for Christmas or donate one to someone in urgent need of light!

Last year I did an installation at @ciffdk for this beautiful project:
‚ÄòI believe that everyone has the basic right to breathe in clean air. So many families around the globe are forced to breathe in toxic kerosene fumes due to the lack of access to electricity. The solar-powered lamps that the Little Sun Project provides can improve their health as well as protect our environment. I hope that the art created by Peter Saville and myself for ENLIGHTENMENT will raise awareness and highlight the impact of the great work that Little Sun does.‚Äô @littlesunenergy
